## 1. UCMDB-SN Integration Design Introduction

This document describes the integration design details of MF UCMDB Version 10.33 with Service Now – Madrid version in the context of the solution at DXC.

1.
  1. 1.1Definitions and Abbreviations

| Term | Definition |
| --- | --- |
| MF | Micro Focus |
| UCMDB | Universal Configuration Management Database |
| CIT | Configuration Item Type |
| CI | Configuration Item |
| SN | ServiceNow |
| TQL | Topology Query Language |

1.
  1. 1.2CMS - Central uCMDB

CMS (Configuration Management System) is a central instance of UCMDB and it differ from UCMDB only conceptually.

There is no difference between CMS and UCMDB; it&#39;s the same product, just a different role. The role of CMS (Central uCMDB) is to capture infrastructure information from different standalone uCMDB and push the same information to Service Now.

By default, UCMDB act as CMS, as a result of its global id generator capabilities which are enabled out of the box

1.
  1. 1.3ServiceNow

ServiceNow is a cloud-based Service Management system that facilitates;

- A greater focus on IT&#39;s relationships with customers (Incident Management, Problem Management, Configuration Management, Change Management, service catalogue, request management)
- IT groups collaborating on Services and processes that cross organizational lines
- IT groups aligning on ITIL V.3 processes

In our context ServiceNow is the consumer and consumes the configuration item and their relationship information from CMS (Central uCMDB) which is a provider of data. Creation of Incident, Problem, Request for Change ticket in ServiceNow based on CI and relationship information pushed by uCMDB.

1.
  1. 1.4Audience

The audiences of this document are the technical members of the DXC

- Below service now credential information to be configured in generic protocol and connection information to be configured in UCMDB Integration Studio

|         **Name** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| Host Name | The host name of the Service Now. |
| Port | The Port number of the Service Now |



**Service Now Prerequisites**

- Enable the multiple insert plug-in.

To enable the multiple insert plug-in:

1. Log in to ServiceNow as an administrator.

2. Go to **System Definition \&gt; Plugins**.

3. Locate **Insert Multiple Web Service** and click it.

4. If the status is inactive, click **Activate/Upgrade**. This action will activate the support for insertMultiple in SOAP.

- Create Inbound Services for all class models that you want to integrate. UCMDB ServiceNowGeneric Adapter contain package called - **UCMDB\_SNOW\_update.zip** which contains ServiceNow Update Sets which will be deployed into service now to create all the necessary inbound services in Service Now.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

- Create transform maps between the staging tables and target tables. UCMDB ServiceNowGeneric Adapter contain package called - **UCMDB\_SNOW\_update.zip** which contains ServiceNow Update Sets which will be deployed into service now to create all the necessary transform maps between the staging tables and target tables in Service Now.

- Create a Role with minimal rights to serve the integration. UCMDB ServiceNowGeneric Adapter contain package called - **UCMDB\_SNOW\_update.zip** which contains ServiceNow Update Sets which will be deployed into service now to create all the necessary roles with appropriate ACL information&#39;s.

1.
  1. 1.7Data Push

 Data Push is the process of pushing data (CIs and Links) to an external data source. The external source may be any source that has an adapter capable of receiving CIs and Links.

In Data Push, a Query is executed on the UCMDB and the result is then pushed to the adapter (Which is responsible to push it the external data source). Data Push is an asynchronous scheduled Task.

In order to define and run the data push, integration point needs to be created in UCMDB.

1.
  1.
    1. 5.1.1CI type mapping

CI type mapping is nothing but the mapping of uCMDB configuration item type to ServiceNow CI Class. In our context, Source CIT of uCMDB is mapped to destination class name of ServiceNow.

**Please not that ServiceNow table can be changed according to the DXC requirement whenever required.**
